rators, spaces, and publics imagined to be harmed by corruption. Corruption Plots demonstrates how corruption talk is leveraged to make sense of unequal spatial change and used opportunistically by those who are themselves implicated in wrongdoing. Offering a wide-ranging analysis of urban worlds, the authors reveal the ethical, spatial, and political stakes of storytelling and how vital it is to examine the "corruption plot" in all its contradictions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCapitalismxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aCorruptionzIndia. 0aEconomic developmentxCorrupt practiceszIndia. 0aLand use, UrbanxEconomic aspectszIndia. 0aPolitical corruptionzIndia. 0aUrbanizationxEconomic aspectszIndia. 4aANTHROPOLOGY. 4aGEOGRAPHY. 4aURBAN STUDIES. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  acorruption and the city, corruption in Mumbai and Bengaluru, corruption and real estate, corruption talk, land grabs and corruption.1 aDoshi, Sapana, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPike, David L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150176876740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501768767423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501768767/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell